import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['miles'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['gas'] = pd.to_numeric(data['gas'], errors='coerce')
    data['miles'] = pd.to_numeric(data['miles'], errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['miles'], data['gas'])
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Gas Used (gallons)')
    plt.title('How does the amount of gas used vary with miles driven?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    avg_miles_per_year = data.groupby('year')['miles'].mean()
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = avg_miles_per_year.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Miles Driven')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average miles driven per year?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(avg_miles_per_year.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {avg_miles_per_year.mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['side'] = data['side'].astype('category')
    if len(data['side'].unique()) > 20:
        data = data.groupby('side').apply(lambda x: x.sample(20))
    chart = data.boxplot(column='miles', by='side', rot=45, fontsize=12)
    chart.set_xlabel('Location', fontsize=12)
    chart.set_ylabel('Miles Driven', fontsize=12)
    chart.set_title('How does the location affect the miles driven?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
